enc_source_verbose(25.10)                            enc_source_verbose(25.10)

Name
       enc_source_verbose

Syntax
        enc_source_verbose <value>

       Type: Integer

       Default: 0

       Controls whether scripts are sourced in quiet or verbose mode:

              * By  default  (0),  files  are  sourced  in quiet mode. This is
                equivalent to source <filename>-quiet.

              * If you set this variable to 1, files are  sourced  in  verbose
                mode. This is equivalent to source <filename>-verbose.

Related Information
              * source

